<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="476" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,913,1444]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,913,940]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
(1) Head narrower than pronotum; (2) forewings with vein separating appendix and first apical cell evanescent apically, appendix and first apical cell membranous; (3) pygofer without distinct hooks; (4) pygofer, in ventral view, with numerous short setae at apex; (5) subgenital plates narrowly separated at base, *widely divergent distally, overlapping pygofer laterally; (6) connective U-shaped, bent into right angle at point of articulation with styles; (7) *style with apex foot-shaped (expanded apically); (8) *aedeagus expanded laterally, in posterior view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="476" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,913,1444]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1094,1120]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">Remarks.</emphasis>
Features marked with an asterisk (*) were added and are present in all species. The following features were removed from the original diagnosis of 
<bibRefCitation author="Blocker, H. D." box="[731,907,1129,1155]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref8509" refString="Blocker, H. D. (1979) The Iassinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) of the western Hemisphere. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 52 (1), 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="1979">Blocker (1979)</bibRefCitation>
: (1) “pygofer with ventral margin expanded at middle third and apical third with excavation between, with apical margin acute at about mid-length”; in the new species the ventral margin of the pygofer lacks a deep excavation and the apex lacks an apical acute projection as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Blocker" authorityYear="1979" box="[181,299,1237,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bertawolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhebala">
<emphasis box="[181,299,1237,1263]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">B. rhebala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; (2) “pygofer with heavily sclerotized area along ventral margin”; absent in the two new species; (3) “subgenital plate widened and triangular apically with inconspicuous “hook-like” area at base”; in the new species the apex of the subgenital plate is rounded, in 
<taxonomicName authority="Domahovski, 2020" authorityName="Domahovski" authorityYear="2020" box="[663,737,1309,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bertawolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[663,737,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">B. lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[743,833,1310,1336]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[743,833,1310,1336]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the subgenital plate is not as wide as in 
<taxonomicName box="[1278,1389,1309,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bertawolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhelala">
<emphasis box="[1278,1389,1309,1335]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">B. rhelala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Domahovski, 2020" authorityName="Domahovski" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,281,1345,1371]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bertawolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grazielia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,281,1345,1371]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">B. grazielia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[287,375,1346,1372]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[287,375,1346,1372]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; the “inconspicuous hook-like area at base” mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Blocker, H. D." box="[1025,1194,1345,1371]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" pagination="1 - 70" refId="ref8509" refString="Blocker, H. D. (1979) The Iassinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) of the western Hemisphere. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 52 (1), 1 - 70." type="journal article" year="1979">Blocker (1979)</bibRefCitation>
(Fig. 168: 65) (which presumably is the apodeme of the subgenital plate), is variable in size, and may be smaller, as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Domahovski, 2020" authorityName="Domahovski" authorityYear="2020" box="[1213,1343,1381,1407]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bertawolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grazielia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1213,1343,1381,1407]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">B. grazielia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1348,1436,1382,1408]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1348,1436,1382,1408]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
in comparison to 
<taxonomicName box="[346,457,1417,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bertawolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhelala">
<emphasis box="[346,457,1417,1443]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">B. rhelala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or strongly developed and directed dorsally as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Domahovski, 2020" authorityName="Domahovski" authorityYear="2020" box="[1024,1099,1417,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Bertawolia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1024,1099,1417,1443]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">B. lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1106,1195,1418,1444]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1106,1195,1418,1444]" pageId="1" pageNumber="476" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
